radiographic_examinations.findings: Appendix is fluid-filled and dilated up to 1.1 cm with wall thickening, hyperemia, and a moderate amount of periappendiceal fat stranding. No drainable fluid collection or extraluminal gas to suggest perforation. Mild focal thickening at the base of the cecum, likely reactive. Visualized lung fields, liver, pancreas, spleen, adrenal glands, kidneys, stomach, small intestine, colon, rectum, urinary bladder, and reproductive organs are all within normal limits.
